SELECT order_id,
       customer_id,
	   DATE_TRUNC('week', order_date):: date AS week_start, -- starting from week_start (monday)
	   order_status,
	   COALESCE(order_amount, 0) AS cleaned_amount, -- replacing null values with 0 for better mathematical calculations
	   payment_method
FROM "ecommerce_orders_analytics"."analytics_raw"."orders"

SELECT order_id,
       week_start,
	   SUM(cleaned_amount) AS weekly_revenue
FROM "ecommerce_orders_analytics"."analytics"."staging_orders"
GROUP BY order_id,
         week_start

select cleaned_amount
from "ecommerce_orders_analytics"."analytics"."staging_orders"
where cleaned_amount is null

select customer_id
from "ecommerce_orders_analytics"."analytics"."staging_orders"
where customer_id is null

select order_id
from "ecommerce_orders_analytics"."analytics"."staging_orders"
where order_id is null

select week_start
from "ecommerce_orders_analytics"."analytics"."staging_orders"
where week_start is null

select
    order_id as unique_field,
    count(*) as n_records

from "ecommerce_orders_analytics"."analytics"."staging_orders"
where order_id is not null
group by order_id
having count(*) > 1

SELECT order_id,
       week_start,
	   weekly_revenue,
	   LAG(weekly_revenue) OVER(PARTITION BY order_id ORDER BY week_start) AS prev_week_revenue
FROM "ecommerce_orders_analytics"."analytics"."weekly_order_revenue"

SELECT order_id,
       week_start,
	   weekly_revenue,
	   LAG(weekly_revenue, 4) OVER(PARTITION BY order_id ORDER BY week_start) AS prev_week4_order_revenue
FROM "ecommerce_orders_analytics"."analytics"."weekly_order_revenue"

SELECT order_id, 
       week_start, 
	   weekly_revenue, 
	   AVG(weekly_revenue) OVER(PARTITION BY order_id ORDER BY week_start ROWS BETWEEN 4 PRECEDING AND 1 PRECEDING) AS rolling_four_weeks_prev, 
	   STDDEV_POP(weekly_revenue) OVER(PARTITION BY order_id ORDER BY week_start ROWS BETWEEN 4 PRECEDING AND 1 PRECEDING) AS stddev_four_weeks_prev
FROM "ecommerce_orders_analytics"."analytics"."weekly_order_revenue"

    1

SELECT order_id,
       week_start,
	   weekly_revenue,
	   prev_week_revenue,
	   week_over_week_percentage_growth,
	   CASE
	       WHEN prev_week_revenue IS NULL THEN 'Insufficient Data'
           WHEN week_over_week_percentage_growth > 0 THEN 'Improving'
		   WHEN week_over_week_percentage_growth < 0 THEN 'Declining'
		   ELSE 'Stable'
	   END AS perc_growth_flag
